metadata.name: Yin and yang
metadata.description:
In Ancient Chinese philosophy, yin and yang (lit. "dark-light", "negative-positive") is a Chinese philosophical concept that describes how obviously opposite or contrary forces may actually be complementary, interconnected, and interdependent in the natural world, and how they may give rise to each other as they interrelate to one another.
